  "wikitext": "\n'''1-2-015\n\nAlternative term: Pilotage service\n\nThe provision of a service of specially qualified men possessing detailed local knowledge, who assist the masters of vessels to navigate them in particular areas.\n\n\nNote: In Britain and the U.S.A. the word \"pilotage\" is also loosely used for piloting.\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Pilotage}}\n[[Category:1.2 Navigation]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]"
